## **1. Understanding xv6 File System Structure**

The xv6 file system has these key components:
- **Superblock**: Contains metadata about the file system (size, number of blocks, etc.)
- **Inode table**: Array of inodes, each representing a file or directory
- **Data blocks**: Where file contents and directory entries are stored
- **Bitmap blocks**: Track free/allocated blocks

Each **inode** contains:
- File type (regular file, directory, device)
- Size
- Link count
- Direct block pointers (12)
- Indirect block pointer
- Double-indirect block pointer

**Directories** are special files containing `struct dirent` entries:
```c
struct dirent {
  ushort inum;    // inode number
  char name[DIRSIZ];  // file name (max 14 chars)
};
```

## **2. Required Tools Implementation**

### **2.1 DirectoryWalker (10%)**
**Purpose**: Recursively traverse and print file system tree
**Implementation**:
```c
// Pseudo-code
void directoryWalker(int fd, uint inum, int depth) {
  // Read inode
  struct dinode din;
  readi(inum, &din);

  if(din.type == T_DIR) {
    // Read directory entries
    for each block in inode {
      for each dirent in block {
        if(dirent.inum != 0) {
          print_indent(depth);
          printf("%s (inode %d)\n", dirent.name, dirent.inum);
          // Recursive call for subdirectories
          if(is_directory(dirent.inum)) {
            directoryWalker(fd, dirent.inum, depth+1);
          }
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
```

### **2.2 ImapWalker (10%)**
**Purpose**: Print all allocated inodes
**Implementation**:
```c
void imapWalker(int fd) {
  // Read superblock
  struct superblock sb;
  read_superblock(fd, &sb);

  // Iterate through inode table
  for(int i = 1; i < sb.ninodes; i++) {
    struct dinode din;
    readi(i, &din);
    if(din.type != 0) {  // Allocated inode
      printf("Inode %d: type=%d, size=%d, links=%d\n", 
             i, din.type, din.size, din.nlink);
    }
  }
}
```

### **2.3 InodeReader (10%)**
**Purpose**: Return detailed information about a specific inode
**Implementation**:
```c
void inodeReader(int fd, uint inum) {
  struct dinode din;
  readi(inum, &din);

  printf("Inode %d:\n", inum);
  printf("  Type: %s\n", din.type == T_DIR ? "Directory" : 
                        din.type == T_FILE ? "File" : "Device");
  printf("  Size: %d bytes\n", din.size);
  printf("  Links: %d\n", din.nlink);
  printf("  Direct blocks: ");
  for(int i = 0; i < NDIRECT; i++) {
    if(din.addrs[i]) printf("%d ", din.addrs[i]);
  }
  printf("\n");

  if(din.addrs[NDIRECT]) {
    printf("  Indirect block: %d\n", din.addrs[NDIRECT]);
    // Could read and print indirect blocks
  }
}
```

